		<description><![CDATA[<p><img align="right" class="alignright  wp-image-4174" src="http://www.makealivingwriting.com/wp-content/uploads/photodune-8742663-happy-business-man-holding-a-umbrella-and-catching-money-rain-xs-e1419447598977.jpg" alt="happy business man holding a umbrella and catching money" width="292" height="438" /></p>
<p>When I started out as a freelance writer, I knew nothing about finding clients that pay well.</p>
<p>I started with bidding sites and general job boards, because I thought it was easy money. But I quickly discovered you can’t <a title="What it Really Takes to Make a Living Writing" href="http://www.makealivingwriting.com/what-it-takes-make-a-living-writing/" target="_blank">build a successful career</a> as an article writer if you’re only earning $5 per article.</p>
<p>It was clear I needed to make more money for each article.</p>
<p>So I stopped hanging out on the bidding sites and targeted higher-paying writing jobs. In one year's time, I went from earning $5 dollars an article on bidding sites to earning $900 for a feature article.</p>
<p>How? Here are the steps I took:</p>
