		<description><![CDATA[<p><img align="right" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-4152" src="http://www.makealivingwriting.com/wp-content/uploads/celebrity-in-crowd1-300x193.jpg" alt="Beautiful blond girl looking like a superstar posing and lots of" width="300" height="193" /></p>
<p>It can be one of the most enjoyable assignments in journalism -- interview movie stars! Or music artists, politicians, magicians, authors, dancers, mega-church pastors. Pick your favorite celebrity flavor.</p>
<p>But it's often difficult to get famous people to grant you an interview. I spent 12 years pursuing CEOs of major corporations for interviews as a staff reporter, and I was a movie-industry secretary for several years, so I speak from experience on both sides of the fence here.</p>
<p>Here's what I learned: To get household names to slot you an interview time, you have to be wily, creative, and unstoppable.</p>
